        <p class="mt-3">"First 3" refers to a specific card game where players are dealt three cards each.</p>
        <p>In this game, the objective is to have the highest-valued card combination among the three cards.</p>
        <p>The player with the highest-ranking card combination wins the round.</p>
        <div class="row">
            <p class="mb-0"><b>METHOD OF PLAY</b></p>
            <p class="text-gray">The game is played using eight (8) decks of cards (52 cards per deck), placed in a shoe, after having been shuffled according to official procedures. One may choose to bet on either side (the GOLD or the SILVER).</p>
            <p class="text-gray">The object of the game is to get the highest hand from the three (3) cards dealt with by the Dealer.</p>
            <p class="mb-0"><b>DEFINITION OF TERMS</b></p>
            <p>
                <b>BETTING LIMIT </b>
                <span class="text-gray">the minimum and maximum amount of bets allowed per game or variant</span>
            </p>
            <p>
                <b>CARD SHOE </b>
                <span class="text-gray">gaming equipment used to contain and enable the dealing of cards</span>
            </p>
            <p>
                <b>DEALER </b>
                <span class="text-gray">a casino employee who conducts the game</span>
            </p>
            <p>
                <b>DIFFERENTIAL BET </b>
                <span class="text-gray">the difference between GOLD and SILVER total bet</span>
            </p>
            <p>
                <b>FACE-UP CARD </b>
                <span class="text-gray">cards discarded after each shuffle together with the top card</span>
            </p>
            <p>
                <b>GAME BURN CARD </b>
                <span class="text-gray">cards whose face values are shown</span>
            </p>
            <p>
                <b>HAND </b>
                <span class="text-gray">combination formed by the three cards dealt</span>
            </p>
            <p>
                <b>INDICATOR/CUT CARD </b>
                <span class="text-gray">thin rectangular piece of plastic, normally bearing five perforations and having the exact dimensions of a playing card, and is used to cut a stack of cards, conceal the value of the last card in a stack, or to indicate the last deal</span>
            </p>
            <p>
                <b>LAYOUT </b>
                <span class="text-gray">the playing area where cards dealt are shown</span>
            </p>
            <p>
                <b>PIP VALUE </b>
                <span class="text-gray">a number on the front side of the card</span>
            </p>
            <p>
                <b>PRIZE POOL </b>
                <span class="text-gray">total bets placed less 5% commission</span>
            </p>
            <p>
                <b>TIE </b>
                <span class="text-gray">a condition where the outcome for both the Gold and Silver is equal.</span>
            </p>
            <p>
                <b>WINNING MARKER </b>
                <span class="text-gray">indicator to determine the winning hand.</span>
            </p>
